attributeList.attribute: CSN4 and CSN6 appear to be required for stabilizing and converting CSN5 into its active state, via rearrangement within CSN5 to open the NEDD8 binding pocket. Full enzymatic activity in vitro requires the complete set of subunits.

Essential regulator of the ubiquitin (Ubl) conjugation pathway by mediating the deneddylation of the cullin subunits of SCF-type E3 ligase complexes. Plays a role in the regulation of the mating pheromone response.
